doc.after: The mistle thrush is hunted by birds of prey including the boreal owl,[27] short-eared owl,[28] tawny owl,[29] Ural owl,[30] Eurasian eagle-owl,[31] golden eagle,[32] kestrel,[15] common buzzard,[33] red kite,[34] northern goshawk,[35] peregrine falcon,[36] and sparrowhawk.[37] The eggs and chicks may be targeted by cats and corvids, although the adults are fearless in defence of their nests, occasionally even attacking humans.[15] The mistle thrush is not normally a host of the common cuckoo, a brood parasite.[38]
